[7] New Zealand (Hawkes Bay)
Date: Mon 22 Jul 2019 18:36 NZST
Source: Stuff [abridged, edited]
https://www.stuff.co.nz/national/health/114425073/twentyeight-in-isolation-at-home-after-second-measles-case-emerges-in-hawkes-bay


Last week [week of 15 Jul 2019] an infant was diagnosed with the measles and admitted to Hawke's Bay Hospital. The child was discharged from hospital on [Mon 22 Jul 2019].

The 2nd confirmed case shared the same family and community networks as the 1st, according to Medical Officer of Health Dr Nicholas Jones.

After health authorities confirmed the 1st case on Friday evening [19 Jul 2019], medical staff spoke to 124 people who had been in contact with the infant. [See source URL above for locations of possible exposure.] 28 people are now in isolation at their homes, according to a statement released by Hawke's Bay DHB [District Health Board] on Monday afternoon [22 Jul 2019]. That covered people who had been in contact with the child and weren't immunised, weren't sure if they were immunised, or had some of the early symptoms of the measles.

